SUBSTITUTE FOR
HOUSE BILL NO. 4511
A bill to prohibit the banning, provision of permitting or
licensure requirements, or provision of other impairments of or for
the holding of digital assets; to prohibit the advocacy or support
through certain actions by certain state governmental officers and
entities of a central bank digital currency by the United States
government; to prohibit the imposition of prohibitions on the
operation of certain nodes related to blockchain protocols, certain
transfers of digital assets on blockchain protocols, or the
participation in staking on certain blockchain protocols; to
prohibit certain civil liability; and to provide for the powers and
duties of certain state and local governmental officers and
entities.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF MICHIGAN ENACT:
BJH H02045'25 (H-1) fbudyn

2
1 Sec. 1. (1) Subject to provisions in the Michigan penal code,
2 1931 PA 328, MCL 750.1 to 750.568, this state or any political
3 subdivision of this state shall not do any of the following with
4 regard to digital assets:
5 (a) Ban the holding of digital assets.
6 (b) Require a person to be granted a permit or license for the
7 holding of digital assets, unless the person is holding the digital
8 assets on behalf of another person.
9 (c) Impose any other impairment for the holding of digital
10 assets.
11 (d) Impose any additional tax, withholding, assessment, or
12 charge that is based solely on the use of the digital asset as the
13 method of payment. This subdivision does not prohibit this state
14 from imposing a tax, withholding, assessment, or charge that would
15 otherwise be imposed if the transaction had taken place with United
16 States legal tender.
17 (2) An agency or department of this state shall not advocate
18 for or support, including by issuing a memorandum or official
19 statement of support from the agency or department or its
20 designees, the testing, adoption, or implementation of a central
21 bank digital currency by the United States government.
22 (3) Subject to provisions in the Michigan penal code, 1931 PA
23 328, MCL 750.1 to 750.568, this state or any political subdivision
24 of this state shall not prohibit any of the following:
25 (a) The operation of a node for the purpose of connecting to a
26 blockchain protocol or a protocol built on top of a blockchain
27 protocol.
28 (b) The transfer of digital assets on a blockchain protocol.
29 (c) The participation in staking on a blockchain protocol.
BJH H02045'25 (H-1) fbudyn

3
1 (4) A person that validates only a transaction for digital
2 asset mining, the operation of a node or series of nodes on a
3 blockchain network, or the provision of digital asset mining or
4 staking services for persons is not civilly liable.
5 (5) As used in this section:
6 (a) "Blockchain" means data that is shared across a network to
7 create a ledger of verified transactions or information among
8 network participants linked using cryptography to maintain the
9 integrity of the ledger and to execute other functions, and
10 distributed among network participants in an automated fashion to
11 concurrently update network participants on the state of the ledger
12 and any other functions.
13 (b) "Blockchain protocol" means any executable software
14 deployed to a blockchain composed of source code that is publicly
15 available and accessible, including a smart contract or any network
16 of smart contracts.
17 (c) "Consensus mechanism" means a protocol or set of protocols
18 that bring all nodes of a blockchain network into agreement to
19 verify the state of a digital ledger.
20 (d) "Digital asset" means virtual currency, cryptocurrencies,
21 and stablecoins.
22 (e) "Digital asset mining" means using electricity to power a
23 computer or node for the purpose of securing a blockchain network.
24 (f) "Holding" means possession, including, but not limited to,
25 electronic possession.
26 (g) "Node" means a computational device that contains and
27 updates a copy of a blockchain.
28 (h) "Smart contract" means a self-executing contract or
29 agreement that is stored on a blockchain network that executes
BJH H02045'25 (H-1) fbudyn

4
1 automatically when the contract's conditions are met.
2 (i) "Staking" means using a node to lock digital assets in
3 order to operate the consensus mechanism of a blockchain protocol.
